536
00:36:59,620 --> 00:37:03,000
We can do it once talks about it surface.

537
00:37:03,000 --> 00:37:09,250
Gosh, but the problem is this film studio is talking about plagiarism.

538
00:37:09,250 --> 00:37:11,780
Does a murder case have copyrights or something, huh?

539
00:37:11,780 --> 00:37:16,390
There are more than a couple of works about serial murder at Hwaseong!

540
00:37:16,390 --> 00:37:20,130
Hey, you still have the first date you wrote your novel on your computer. Right?

541
00:37:21,520 --> 00:37:22,640
Why do you ask?

542
00:37:22,640 --> 00:37:26,540
Even in my opinion, the description of the murder is too similar to our novel.

543
00:37:26,540 --> 00:37:29,160
If a dispute happens, it'll be a huge headache.

544
00:37:29,160 --> 00:37:32,290
So let's strike them first and get it over with.

545
00:37:32,290 --> 00:37:35,190
If we can prove the novel was written before the scenario—

546
00:37:35,190 --> 00:37:37,800
Let's just stop this novel.

547
00:37:37,800 --> 00:37:39,100
What?

548
00:37:39,100 --> 00:37:42,610
You're telling me to prove my work to be mine.

549
00:37:42,610 --> 00:37:45,180
I can't do that because my pride won't allow it.

550
00:37:45,180 --> 00:37:47,050
So l-let's stop with this novel.

551
00:37:47,050 --> 00:37:48,890
What do you mean by that?

552
00:37:48,890 --> 00:37:52,760
There's no reason for me to prove it wasn't plagiarized!

553
00:37:52,760 --> 00:37:54,080
Nor do I want to prove it!

554
00:37:54,080 --> 00:37:57,000
I'd rather stop selling it than hear that!

555
00:37:57,000 --> 00:37:59,470
Stop the sales! At once!

556
00:37:59,470 --> 00:38:01,280
Hey, why are you being so emotional—

557
00:38:01,280 --> 00:38:02,780
I'm naturally emotional!

558
00:38:02,780 --> 00:38:05,370
- Hey, you've misunderstood. Sit down— 
 - No, stop the sales! The end! I'm done!

559
00:38:05,370 --> 00:38:08,580
Hey, Dong Joo!

560
00:38:08,580 --> 00:38:10,510
Geez!

561
00:38:12,730 --> 00:38:15,640
- Writer— 
 - Okay, take care.

562
00:38:22,010 --> 00:38:23,620
What's wrong with Writer Yook?

563
00:38:23,620 --> 00:38:26,870
Did you check who owns the copyright...

564
00:38:26,870 --> 00:38:29,270
to Director Shin's scenario?

565
00:38:29,270 --> 00:38:33,880
Since they haven't signed a contract with the film studio, Director Shin's family must have it.

566
00:38:33,880 --> 00:38:36,910
Please contact the bereaved family...

567
00:38:38,660 --> 00:38:40,690
and schedule a meeting.

568
00:38:40,690 --> 00:38:41,990
Sorry?

569
00:38:41,990 --> 00:38:47,130
Let's j-just buy this scenario's copyright...

570
00:38:47,130 --> 00:38:49,250
and settle all of this.

571
00:38:50,720 --> 00:38:52,700
Understood.

572
00:38:57,560 --> 00:39:00,420
That nutcase, seriously...

573
00:39:02,640 --> 00:39:05,080
Gosh...

574
00:39:13,240 --> 00:39:15,850
Man, did I come off too strong?

575
00:39:16,530 --> 00:39:18,360
Geez...

576
00:39:20,540 --> 00:39:21,400
   

577
00:39:22,380 --> 00:39:24,350
Where are you?

578
00:39:25,310 --> 00:39:27,200
The police station?

579
00:39:27,200 --> 00:39:29,620
Why don't you answer me?

580
00:39:29,620 --> 00:39:32,440
Why were you tailing that student?

581
00:39:32,440 --> 00:39:36,340
What were you planning to do to her, huh?

582
00:39:37,830 --> 00:39:40,650
There must be a reason you were following her.

583
00:39:40,650 --> 00:39:42,650
 Because you tried to die. 

584
00:39:43,970 --> 00:39:46,640
 I followed you just in case you killed yourself. 

585
00:39:46,640 --> 00:39:48,680
 I wanted to stop you. 

586
00:39:49,730 --> 00:39:53,900
Are you going to keep quiet?

587
00:39:53,900 --> 00:39:56,850
Why do you care whether I die or not?

588
00:39:58,320 --> 00:40:01,020
You're a stalker, aren't you?

589
00:40:01,020 --> 00:40:03,520
How did you know I was trying to die?

590
00:40:03,520 --> 00:40:04,450
Young lady?

591
00:40:04,450 --> 00:40:06,250
 So what if your grades fall a bit? 

592
00:40:06,250 --> 00:40:09,050
They can't go any lower!

593
00:40:09,050 --> 00:40:12,710
I'm terrified at the thought of my parents being disappointed.

594
00:40:12,710 --> 00:40:15,510
They compare me to my brother and belittle me.

595
00:40:15,510 --> 00:40:18,150
I no longer want to live like this.

596
00:40:18,150 --> 00:40:20,620
Dying is the easier option.

597
00:40:21,950 --> 00:40:24,970
 Why did you come to the police station if you wanted to die? 

598
00:40:29,080 --> 00:40:32,980
I was scared because you kept following me.

599
00:40:32,980 --> 00:40:35,870
 Why were you scared if you were going to die? 

600
00:40:35,870 --> 00:40:38,410
 Live as if you're dead. 

601
00:40:39,290 --> 00:40:41,440
 Live for yourself... 

602
00:40:41,440 --> 00:40:43,540
 not for others. 

603
00:40:44,440 --> 00:40:46,730
 Dying is scarier. 

604
00:40:51,960 --> 00:40:53,560
Young lady.

605
00:40:53,560 --> 00:40:55,300
What are you doing right now?

606
00:40:55,300 --> 00:40:58,660
By chance... are you sick?

607
00:40:59,560 --> 00:41:00,760
No.

608
00:41:01,930 --> 00:41:04,110
Your parents aren't picking up their phones.

609
00:41:04,110 --> 00:41:07,240
- I'll try them one more time, so— 
 - It's okay. Don't call them.

610
00:41:07,240 --> 00:41:08,780
No, no.

611
00:41:08,780 --> 00:41:11,310
There's the situation with him...

612
00:41:11,310 --> 00:41:14,340
- and you're also a bit— 
 - I was just playing around.

613
00:41:14,340 --> 00:41:16,020
Playing around?

614
00:41:16,020 --> 00:41:18,020
We're friends.

615
00:41:20,500 --> 00:41:22,600
I'm sorry.

616
00:41:22,600 --> 00:41:23,710
No, no.

617
00:41:23,710 --> 00:41:26,230
Wait here until your parents get here.

618
00:41:26,230 --> 00:41:28,770
Young lady! Wait!

619
00:41:28,770 --> 00:41:31,280
Young lady, where are you going?

620
00:41:48,530 --> 00:41:51,310
You've added stalking to your to-do list now?

621
00:41:51,310 --> 00:41:53,510
I was looking for the right timing, not stalking her.

622
00:41:53,510 --> 00:41:54,480
What timing?

623
00:41:54,480 --> 00:41:57,560
To stop something that can't be undone from happening.

624
00:41:57,560 --> 00:42:00,670
You're able to stop time, too?

625
00:42:00,670 --> 00:42:02,200
She's coming.

626
00:42:02,200 --> 00:42:04,700
- Who is? 
 - Wait!

627
00:42:21,050 --> 00:42:23,160
Give me your cell phone.

628
00:42:37,110 --> 00:42:39,100
I'll katalk you. 
  (Korean SMS) 

629
00:42:39,100 --> 00:42:40,330
Katalk?

630
00:42:40,330 --> 00:42:41,480
Don't brush me off.

631
00:42:41,480 --> 00:42:44,620
If you do, I'll expose your secret.

632
00:42:44,620 --> 00:42:47,890
   

633
00:42:47,890 --> 00:42:50,190
   

634
00:42:51,450 --> 00:42:53,280
What's katalk?

635
00:42:54,330 --> 00:42:56,910
Oh, that means she wants to date you.

636
00:42:57,970 --> 00:42:59,540
What about "brushing her off"?

637
00:42:59,540 --> 00:43:01,320
You'll die if you reject her.

638
00:43:01,320 --> 00:43:02,750
What?

639
00:43:02,750 --> 00:43:05,000
Let's go eat.

640
00:43:09,960 --> 00:43:12,590
   

