667
00:45:32,340 --> 00:45:34,690
 Do you know something? 

668
00:45:34,690 --> 00:45:36,060
 Huh? 

669
00:45:39,600 --> 00:45:41,070
 Hold on. 

670
00:45:41,070 --> 00:45:42,720
 Hyungnim! 

671
00:45:47,440 --> 00:45:49,060
Of course, I know him.

672
00:45:49,060 --> 00:45:51,570
He was a brilliant student at the top of his class.

673
00:45:51,570 --> 00:45:52,570
Is that so?

674
00:45:52,570 --> 00:45:57,390
Except for once or twice in the 12th grade, he always ranked number one in class.

675
00:45:57,390 --> 00:46:01,580
As you may know, our school is prestigious, so placing first here means nationally—

676
00:46:01,580 --> 00:46:03,440
The school has a contact network. Right?

677
00:46:03,440 --> 00:46:06,130
I'd like to obtain this student's contact info.

678
00:46:06,780 --> 00:46:09,000
He's been reported missing.

679
00:46:10,540 --> 00:46:12,290
Missing?

680
00:46:12,290 --> 00:46:14,760
Some say he's dead.

681
00:46:14,760 --> 00:46:17,000
When was that?

682
00:46:22,490 --> 00:46:26,130
Didn't you say you like rice?

683
00:46:26,130 --> 00:46:28,230
I like hamburgers, too.

684
00:46:28,230 --> 00:46:33,030
Why a hamburger when I was going to buy you top-quality beef?

685
00:46:33,030 --> 00:46:35,190
Hyung, do you have any siblings?

686
00:46:35,190 --> 00:46:37,240
No.

687
00:46:37,240 --> 00:46:40,070
How old were you when your father passed away?

688
00:46:40,070 --> 00:46:41,810
Five years old.

689
00:46:41,810 --> 00:46:43,900
You must not remember him that well.

690
00:46:43,900 --> 00:46:46,090
That's right.

691
00:46:46,090 --> 00:46:48,190
Why don't you live with your mom?

692
00:46:48,190 --> 00:46:51,390
Find yourself instead of questioning me.

693
00:46:51,390 --> 00:46:53,440
Hang a banner first thing tomorrow.

694
00:46:53,440 --> 00:46:54,870
Since I need to find myself.

695
00:46:54,870 --> 00:46:58,370
I ought to hang that banner to stop your nagging.

696
00:47:02,210 --> 00:47:05,700
I'm really curious about this.

697
00:47:05,700 --> 00:47:09,530
What does it feel like to have no memories?

698
00:47:14,550 --> 00:47:18,210
I guess you can say it's like being a young child.

699
00:47:18,210 --> 00:47:20,650
To be specific?

700
00:47:20,650 --> 00:47:23,850
Each built-up memory makes you who you are.

701
00:47:23,850 --> 00:47:27,350
But you have to learn something new each day since you have no memories.

702
00:47:27,350 --> 00:47:29,330
Like a young child.

703
00:47:29,330 --> 00:47:31,190
That's true.

704
00:47:31,190 --> 00:47:34,860
There are dots scattered everywhere,

705
00:47:34,860 --> 00:47:37,970
but it's frustrating because they don't align.

706
00:47:37,970 --> 00:47:41,360
So, you have these so-called scattered dots?

707
00:47:45,130 --> 00:47:47,160
 I'm sorry. 

708
00:47:49,820 --> 00:47:52,410
 I'm sorry, little brother. 

709
00:47:58,230 --> 00:48:00,430
I'm somewhat jealous.

710
00:48:00,430 --> 00:48:01,970
Of what?

711
00:48:01,970 --> 00:48:05,750
You don't have any memories you want to forget or erase.

712
00:48:05,750 --> 00:48:10,220
You just need to build good memories from now on.

713
00:48:11,230 --> 00:48:14,520
Memories are quite wicked.

714
00:48:15,210 --> 00:48:19,150
The memories I want to keep become hazy,

715
00:48:19,150 --> 00:48:24,270
and the ones I'm embarrassed about and want to erase keep popping up.

716
00:48:25,690 --> 00:48:28,310
I guess you can be serious at times, too.

717
00:48:28,310 --> 00:48:31,560
Jerk me around, why don't you?

718
00:48:34,710 --> 00:48:37,500
What do you think about Lightning?

719
00:48:37,500 --> 00:48:38,700
What do you mean?

720
00:48:38,700 --> 00:48:39,890
Your name.

721
00:48:39,890 --> 00:48:42,470
Since you appeared after being hit by lightning.

722
00:48:42,470 --> 00:48:44,180
I don't like it.

723
00:48:44,180 --> 00:48:46,620
What about Thunder?

724
00:48:46,620 --> 00:48:51,370
Hey, Meteor sounds nice, right? Meteor since you fell out of the sky.

725
00:48:51,370 --> 00:48:53,890
How did you become a writer?

726
00:48:54,960 --> 00:48:58,280
Beats me. It happened, thanks to you. Gosh...

727
00:48:59,460 --> 00:49:01,070
Me?

728
00:49:01,780 --> 00:49:03,920
Hey, Deok Boon sounds good. 
  (Means "Thanks to...") 

729
00:49:03,920 --> 00:49:08,410
Since you appeared like a revelation of God, so Shin Deok Boon. 
  (Shin means "God.") 

730
00:49:09,480 --> 00:49:10,800
How about Cut?

731
00:49:10,800 --> 00:49:12,010
Cut?

732
00:49:12,010 --> 00:49:13,160
Cut-the-crap.

733
00:49:13,160 --> 00:49:14,560
Get over here!

734
00:49:14,560 --> 00:49:16,830
You're getting cheeky.

735
00:49:16,830 --> 00:49:18,510
Hey, what about No-name?

736
00:49:18,510 --> 00:49:20,570
Since you don't have a name.

737
00:49:20,570 --> 00:49:23,810
It's the best so far.

738
00:49:23,810 --> 00:49:27,700
Since you're a miracle boy who came back from the dead, how does Gi Jeok sound? 
  (Gi Jeok means "miracle.") 

739
00:49:27,760 --> 00:49:30,240
Gi Jeok. Gi Jeok, Gi Jeok...

740
00:49:30,240 --> 00:49:33,520
Gosh, that won't work. It sounds like a diaper.

741
00:49:42,330 --> 00:49:44,440
Whoa.

742
00:49:44,440 --> 00:49:46,520
This is your office?

743
00:49:46,520 --> 00:49:49,000
It's so grand.

744
00:49:49,000 --> 00:49:51,140
It's just spacious. There's nothing much else.

745
00:49:51,140 --> 00:49:53,150
And it's not even mine.

746
00:49:53,930 --> 00:49:56,410
Change into my clothes for now

747
00:49:56,410 --> 00:50:00,160
and let's shop for your clothes and necessities tomorrow.

748
00:50:00,160 --> 00:50:04,280
I'll leave once I find my family, so let's just buy what I need.

749
00:50:08,480 --> 00:50:11,210
You read all of these books?

750
00:50:11,210 --> 00:50:14,390
Books aren't meant to be read in the first place.

751
00:50:14,390 --> 00:50:18,970
They provide inner peace just by being there.

752
00:50:18,970 --> 00:50:22,620
Also, that's your bedroom.

753
00:50:22,620 --> 00:50:25,160
But your bed is coming tomorrow.

754
00:50:25,160 --> 00:50:27,880
So you can sleep on the couch today.

755
00:50:27,880 --> 00:50:28,960
Don't you have a blanket?

756
00:50:28,960 --> 00:50:31,010
I can just sleep on the floor with a blanket.

757
00:50:31,010 --> 00:50:33,750
Blanket, my ass.

758
00:50:33,750 --> 00:50:37,340
Also, this is my workspace.

759
00:50:37,340 --> 00:50:40,820
So absolutely don't intrude.

760
00:50:40,820 --> 00:50:42,840
What's that?

761
00:50:42,840 --> 00:50:45,210
It's a laptop. What else?

762
00:50:48,130 --> 00:50:49,340
Gosh, seriously.

763
00:50:49,340 --> 00:50:53,450
Don't come in here since it's my workspace.

764
00:50:53,450 --> 00:50:57,000
Do I need to put a partition here?

765
00:51:00,750 --> 00:51:03,160
I'm sure I locked it.

766
00:51:03,910 --> 00:51:05,440
What's wrong?

767
00:51:05,440 --> 00:51:06,300
Huh?

768
00:51:06,300 --> 00:51:09,140
N-No, it's nothing.

769
00:51:17,660 --> 00:51:21,910
   

770
00:51:23,400 --> 00:51:25,820
I mean...

771
00:51:25,820 --> 00:51:27,330
I don't need anything else.

772
00:51:27,330 --> 00:51:29,880
Just find what I told you.

773
00:51:30,340 --> 00:51:32,600
Yes, okay.

774
00:51:32,600 --> 00:51:34,700
What are you looking for?

775
00:51:34,700 --> 00:51:35,660
They're still not here?

776
00:51:35,660 --> 00:51:38,390
What are you going to do with the videotape?

777
00:51:38,390 --> 00:51:41,440
The statute of limitations is up anyway.

778
00:51:47,610 --> 00:51:49,570
The rats will hear you.

779
00:51:49,570 --> 00:51:51,690
Watch what you say.

780
00:51:53,070 --> 00:51:55,120
Be honest with me.

781
00:51:59,430 --> 00:52:02,070
You killed Jeon Doo Hyeon, huh?

782
00:52:11,110 --> 00:52:13,650
Well, I know who killed him.

783
00:52:21,360 --> 00:52:23,350
You're not the one, are you?

784
00:52:27,400 --> 00:52:29,290
Goodness!

785
00:52:30,780 --> 00:52:33,490
Sorry to make you wait.

786
00:52:33,490 --> 00:52:36,430
Welcome, Assemblyman Byeon.

787
00:52:37,670 --> 00:52:40,120
Smile a little.

